From: Joel Wiramu Pauling <aenertia@aenertia.net>
Subject: net: airoha: add eBPF soft hook for selective NPU flow offloading

Add Netfilter hooks in airoha_ppe.c that intercept packets marked by a
TC/BPF ingress program and program the NPU TCAM for hardware offloading:

  - NF_INET_FORWARD (mark 0xAF00): L3 routed IPv4/IPv6 flows.
    Extracts NAT reply tuples from conntrack. Works for wired (HWNAT),
    WiFi with WED (CDM4 auto-detected via dev_fill_forward_path), and
    WiFi without WED (6GHz loopback via GDM2).

  - NF_BR_FORWARD (mark 0xAF01): L2 bridged flows (wired↔WiFi).
    Creates PPE_PKT_TYPE_BRIDGE entries in ppe->l2_flows. The PPE's
    existing unbind mechanism creates L3/L4 subflows on demand.

For WiFi interfaces where WED is broken (6GHz HWRRO V3 vs V3.1
mismatch), the worker automatically falls back to NPU loopback: the
PPE rewrites headers and routes to GDM2, the CPU bridge-forwards the
already-rewritten packet to WiFi. This achieves NPU offloading at
~10% CPU (bridge forwarding only) vs 100% CPU (full routing/NAT).

Also increases AIROHA_RX_HEADROOM in airoha_eth.c for future native
XDP support.

Signed-off-by: Joel Wiramu Pauling <aenertia@aenertia.net>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.c |   7 +-
 drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c | 330 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 336 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.c
@@ -18,7 +18,12 @@
-#define AIROHA_RX_HEADROOM		(NET_SKB_PAD + NET_IP_ALIGN)
+/*
+ * Increase Rx headroom to support bpf_xdp_adjust_meta() and future
+ * native XDP. 256 bytes is the standard XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM.
+ */
+#define AIROHA_RX_HEADROOM		(XDP_PACKET_HEADROOM + NET_SKB_PAD + \
+					 NET_IP_ALIGN)
 
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -5,6 +5,12 @@
 #include "airoha_regs.h"
 #include "airoha_eth.h"
 
+#include <net/netfilter/nf_conntrack.h>
+#include <linux/netfilter.h>
+#include <linux/netfilter_bridge.h>
+#include <linux/ip.h>
+#include <linux/ipv6.h>
+
 static DEFINE_MUTEX(flow_offload_mutex);
 static DEFINE_SPINLOCK(ppe_lock);
 
@@ -35,6 +41,320 @@
  * ... existing airoha_ppe.c code ...
